At 12:26 PM 3/16/2010, you wrote:
>I ask this because in trying to get the 7mm hose on the cold start
>valve, it is extremely difficult and I'm afraid I'll break the plastic cold
>start valve fitting.  thanks, greg t.

Use a Q-tip with a teeny bit of silicon grease (Sil-Glyde) to put a 
light film inside the hose end. Slips right on, very much like K-Y 
Jelly when used for it's stated purpose, very very nice, indeed. 
